Class AeDelegatingProcessManager

java.lang.Object
  org.activebpel.rt.bpel.server.engine.recovery.test.AeDelegatingManager
      org.activebpel.rt.bpel.server.engine.recovery.test.AeDelegatingProcessManager
All Implemented Interfaces:
IAeManager, IAeProcessManager
Direct Known Subclasses:
AeDelegatingPersistentProcessManager
public class AeDelegatingProcessManager
extends AeDelegatingManager
implements IAeProcessManager

Implements a process manager that delegates all method calls to an underlying delegate process manager.

getProcessNoUpdate

public IAeBusinessProcess getProcessNoUpdate(long aProcessId)
                                      throws AeBusinessProcessException
Description copied from interface: IAeProcessManager
Returns the business process with the specified process id, locking the process into memory. Each call to IAeProcessManager.getProcessNoUpdate(long) must be followed eventually by a matching call to IAeProcessManager.releaseProcess(IAeBusinessProcess). Calling IAeProcessManager.getProcessNoUpdate(long) instead of IAeProcessManager.getProcess(long) asserts that the caller will not modify the process, so that the process manager may discard the process from memory after it is released without updating its persistent representation (if there is one).

Specified by:
getProcessNoUpdate in interface IAeProcessManager
Parameters:
aProcessId -
Throws:
AeBusinessProcessException
See Also:
IAeProcessManager.getProcessNoUpdate(long)
